iv><div n="meta.9088" type="history" subtype="locations" org="uniform" part="N" sample="complete"><p><geogName type="nome" cert="high" full="yes">Arsinoites</geogName>, <geogName type="ancientRegion" key="Aegyptus" cert="high" full="yes">Egypt</geogName></p></div><div n="tran.9088" type="translation" lang="de" org="uniform" part="N" sample="complete"><p>
            <milestone unit="line" n="1"/>An Severus Iustus, den 
            <app type="BGU"><lem><term lang="la" target="hekatontarches"><foreign lang="la">centurio</foreign></term></lem><wit><bibl default="NO">BL I, S. 17. </bibl></wit></app>,
            <milestone unit="line" n="2" rend="break"/>von Aurelius Abûs, dem Veteranen. <milestone unit="line" n="3"/>Als ich Militärdienst 
            leistete, Herr, in Pêlûsion, gab ich einem gewissen Petesûchos, meinem Kameraden und Freund, 
            Gegenstände im Wert von achthundert Drachmen zur Aufbewahrung. <milestone unit="line" n="9"/>Ich wurde in die
            <app><lem><term target="aleboukontion">ala</term></lem><wit><bibl default="NO"/></wit></app> 
            <term target="aleboukontion">Vocontiorum</term> versetzt, und als ich mit ihm wegen 
            dieser Dinge eine Abrechnung machen wollte nach unser beider Entlassung, machte er mir keine 
            Abrechnung. <milestone unit="line" n="15"/>Hiermit ersuche ich, wobei ich als Zeugen Syriôn, Sohn des 
            Is[i]dôros, <app><lem>aus K[aran]is</lem><wit><bibl default="NO"/></wit></app> habe <app><lem>, der (mir) zustimmte, darum, 
                [daß sie Dir vorgeführt werden – – –]</lem><wit><bibl default="NO"/></wit></app>
        </p></div><div n="tran.9088" type="translation" lang="en" org="uniform" part="N" sample="complete"><p>
            <milestone unit="line" n="1"/>To Severus Iustus, 
            <app type="BGU"><lem><term lang="la" target="hekatontarches"><foreign lang="la">centurio</foreign></term></lem><wit><bibl default="NO">BL I 17. </bibl></wit></app>,
            <milestone unit="line" n="2" rend="break"/>from Aurelius Abous, veteran. <milestone unit="line" n="3"/>When I was serving in the army, 
            lord, in Pelusium, I deposited with Petesouchos, a certain fellow soldier and friend of mine 
            objects at a value of eight hundred drachmas. <milestone unit="line" n="9"/>After I had been transferred to 
            the <term target="aleboukontion">ala Vocontiorum</term> and as I was settling accounts 
            with him concerning these things after our discharge, he took no account of me. 
            <milestone unit="line" n="15"/>Therefore I request, since I have a <app><lem>witness</lem><wit><bibl default="NO"/></wit></app>, Syrion, son 
            of Is[i]doros 
            <app><lem>from K[arani]s, who agrees (with me), [that they be brought before you]</lem><wit><bibl default="NO"/></wit></app>
        </p></div></body></text></TEI.2>